nodes.bodyText:
I could add something like that, but I think the typical use case will involve customers setting the proxy settings at the MultiplexingClient level, and not also setting them at each device client level. Because of that, if I add a warning log here, customers will hit it even when using our library correctly.
MultiplexingClient multiplexingClient = new MultiplexingClient(protocol, someProxySettings);
DeviceClient[] multiplexedDeviceClients = new DeviceClient[MULTIPLEXED_DEVICE_CLIENT_COUNT];

for (int i = 0; i < MULTIPLEXED_DEVICE_CLIENT_COUNT; i++)
{
    //Users would have to do this to avoid the warning log if we add it, which feels unnecessary
    multiplexedDeviceClients.setProxySettings(someProxySettings);
}

